        "action": {
          "type": "get message",
          "content": "To make a play that people will love,\nYou must first learn to be a fool.\nForget the logic, drop the clue,\nAnd let the nonsense flow like glue.\n\nIf you want them to weep and wail,\nMake sure the plot is utterly stale.\nNo rising action, no surprise,\nJust a character who never dies.\n\nThe hero must be deeply flawed,\nWith terrible decisions made.\nHe should scream at clouds and talk to trees,\nWhile ignoring all the obvious clues.\n\nGive them a villain, but make him nice,\nWith a heart of gold and gentle eyes.\nLet the good guy lose every fight,\nAnd spend the whole act in the dark of night.\n\nThe dialogue must be nonsensical,\nA jumble of words, quite ridiculous.\n\"Blue is the color of my pain,\"\nSays the protagonist, quite insane.\n\nNo moral lesson, no clear theme,\nJust a chaotic, messy dream.\nIf the audience leaves knowing what's right,\nYou have failed to make it right.\n\nSo tear the script, burn the stage,\nAnd create a world of pure disgrace.\nFor art is not about being true,\nBut making the audience feel like you.\n",
          "label": "response"
        }
      },
